<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-05-24"><hi rend="italic">May 24,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 251.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to instruction No. 236, of March
                            20 last, directing you to inform the Government of Honduras that the
                            Government of the United States insists upon the payment of an indemnity
                            of $10,000 for the murder of Frank Pears, I have now to inquire if the
                            Government of Honduras has made answer to that demand? If it has not,
                            you will remind it of the importance of the matter.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>